1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,329
Step one, believe it can be done.

2
00:00:03,840 --> 00:00:05,570
Here is a basic truth.

3
00:00:05,760 --> 00:00:09,730
To do anything, we must first believe it can be done.

4
00:00:10,079 --> 00:00:15,249
Believing something can be done sets the mind in motion to find a way to do it.

5
00:00:15,599 --> 00:00:21,650
To illustrate this point of creative thinking in training sessions, I often use this example.

6
00:00:21,999 --> 00:00:29,330
I ask the group, how many of you feel it is possible to eliminate jails within the next 30 years?

7
00:00:29,919 --> 00:00:37,409
Invariably, the group looks bewildered, not quite sure they heard right and thinking they are listening to a real fuzzbrain.

8
00:00:37,599 --> 00:00:46,050
So, after a pause, I repeat, how many of you feel it is possible to eliminate jails within the next thirty years?

9
00:00:46,639 --> 00:00:51,650
Once they're sure I'm not joking, someone always blasts me with something like,

10
00:00:51,759 --> 00:00:56,689
you mean to say you want to turn all those murderers, thieves, and rapists loose?

11
00:00:56,799 --> 00:00:59,090
Don't you realize what this would mean?

12
00:00:59,120 --> 00:01:00,930
Why none of us would be safe.

13
00:01:01,120 --> 00:01:02,770
We have to have jails.

14
00:01:03,279 --> 00:01:05,090
Then the others cut loose.

15
00:01:05,279 --> 00:01:08,610
All order would break down if we didn't have jails.

16
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:11,330
Some people are born criminals.

17
00:01:11,599 --> 00:01:13,890
If anything, we need more jails.

18
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:19,249
Did you read in this morning's paper about that murder?" And the group goes on,

19
00:01:19,439 --> 00:01:23,490
telling me all sorts of good reasons why we must have jails.

20
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:30,210
One fellow even suggested we've got to have jails so the police and prison guards can have jobs.

21
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:36,689
After about ten minutes of letting the group prove why we can't eliminate the need for jails,

22
00:01:36,799 --> 00:01:43,969
I say to them, Now, let me mention here that this question of eliminating jails is used to make a point.

23
00:01:44,319 --> 00:01:49,090
Each of you has come up with reasons why we can't eliminate the need for jails.

24
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,930
Will you do me a favor?

25
00:01:51,120 --> 00:01:56,770
Will you try extra hard for a few minutes to believe we can eliminate jails?

26
00:01:57,680 --> 00:02:04,450
Joining in the spirit of the experiment, the group says, in effect, all well, but just for kicks.

27
00:02:04,639 --> 00:02:10,450
Then I ask, now, assuming we can eliminate jails, how could we begin?

